ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime

ElementDescription: First, is this person the same person you told us about earlier?
Is there someone different you can tell us about who was thinking about, considering, or planning to kill themselves but did not try?
What was your relationship with this person who was thinking about suicide?
Notes: 1= Friend you know in person; 2= Friend you only know online; 3= Romantic partner or someone you were dating (or -ex); 4= Brother or sister; 5= Other family member under the age of 18; 6= Parent or another caregiver; 7= Other adult family member; 8= Student in my school; 9= Co-worker

ElementDescription: What was your relationship with this person who was thinking about suicide? : Someone else, please specify
How close were you with this person when this was happening?
Notes: 1= Not at all close; 2= Somewhat close; 3= Very close; 4= Extremely close

ElementDescription: Do you think it is easier for this person to talk with you about their thoughts of suicide if you were online or in person (like when you're at each other's house)?
Notes: 1= Online; 2= In person; 3= No difference; 4= We don't talk online; 5= We don't talk in person; 6= We don't talk in person or online

ElementDescription: How long ago did this person start thinking about suicide?
Notes: 1= 0-6 months ago; 2= 6 months to 12 months ago; 3=1 year to 2 years ago; 4=2 years to 5 years ago; 5= 5 years to 10 years ago; 6= More than 10 years ago

ElementDescription: For how long was this person thinking about suicide?
Notes: 1= 1 day; 2= 2-6 days; 3= 7-13 days (less than 2 weeks); 4= 14-29 days (2 weeks to less than 1 month); 5= 1-3 months; 6= 4-6 months; 7= 7-12 months; 8= Longer than 12 months (more than 1 year); 9= Still happening

ElementDescription: Are you still worried that this person will try to kill themselves?
Did you learn about this as it was starting or after it had already been going on for a while? Your best guess is fine
Notes: 1= As it was starting; 2= After it started but was still happening; 3= After it was over

ElementDescription: How did you learn about this: The person told me directly
How did you learn about this: I saw it happen
How did you learn about this: I saw cuts or scars on their body

How did you learn about this: Someone else told me
How did you learn about this: They just weren't acting like themselves
How did you learn about this: I saw comments/posts on social media
How did you learn about this: Some other way (please specify)
How did this person tell you?
Notes: 1= Through text messaging; 2= In person; 3= Through a social media app like Snapchat; 4= Through direct messaging

ElementDescription: How did this person tell you: Some other way (please specify)
How upset did you feel about this person's thoughts of suicide?
Notes: 1= Not at all upset; 2= Somewhat upset; 3= Upset; 4= Very upset; 5= Extremely upset

ElementDescription: How scared did this make you feel?
Notes: 1= Not at all scared; 2= Somewhat scared; 3= Scared; 4= Very scared; 5= Extremely scared

ElementDescription: Which statement best describes the effect of the person's thoughts of suicide on your life?
Notes: 1= It had little effect on my life; 2= It had somewhat of an effect on me but did not disrupt my life; 3= It disrupted my life for a short time; 4= It disrupted my life in a significant or devastating way; but I no longer feel that way; 5= It had a significant or devastating effect on my that I still feel
